rules.natural: Either animal1 undergoes veterinarian review or animal1 undergoes lab analysis.
Whenever animal1 undergoes lab analysis, if animal1 does not show symptoms or test positive, then animal1 does not require treatment.
If animal1 undergoes first inspection, then animal1 is not approved for release.
Under the condition that animal1 undergoes second inspection, animal1 is not approved for release.
Whenever animal1 undergoes senior veterinarian review, animal1 undergoes first inspection.
Either animal1 undergoes senior veterinarian review or animal1 receives health board approval.
If animal1 receives health board approval, then animal1 undergoes second inspection.
Provided that animal1's quarantine is extended, it is not the case that animal1 completes isolation period.
If animal1 has conflicting reports, then animal1 is safe to release.
Either animal1 has conflicting reports or animal1's quarantine is extended.
